node.text: We had a blast in Jamaica and we can’t wait to do it again. As promised, I uploaded a full review of the resort we stayed in, and I just dropped an entire vlog on YouTube of our stay in Jamaica. Head to my website at thatnursecooks.com to check it out!!! Link in bio!!

node.text:
So I got up this morning to get the kids ready and realized I forgot to buy milk last night 😱 Then I remembered the instant porridges that the lovely team at @gracefoods gave to me and I thought well they can eat this! It was their first time trying it and they loved it! You know I always make porridge for them so if they liked this, then it must be really good! Definitely adding this to my list of quick breakfasts for those school mornings when I’m short on time! .

node.text:
How do you prefer your curry goat or chicken? With white rice or boiled food? Ever feel for something nice? Yep, me too. Curry goat with a few flour dumpling & green banana…and of course some white rice for these kids who don’t yet appreciate the goodness of boiled food! I’ve been toasting organic curry leaves with some curry: excellent flavor boost. I rinsed my banana with baking soda, water, & vinegar because I boil it in the same pot with the dumplings. (Cmon less dishes) Subscribe to my 🎥YouTube channel: thatnursecancook! Recipes are there! Google thatnursecancook and the dish you’re looking for if you can’t find it!
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
On Mondays we prep! Prep work is extremely therapeutic for me. Once a month I take the time to prep my green seasoning, my pickle, and escovitch sauce. This past week I finally put the finishing touches on my biggest project to date. I embarked on this journey late last year and needless to say, it hasn’t been an easy road. The past few months have been extremely hard for me, but cooking has remained my outlet to express myself and share my passion with you all. I’m not sharing the recipe for my pickle & escovitch sauce just yet but you can find the recipe for my green seasoning which is my version of haitian epis on my youtube channel: thatnursecancook. If you’re having trouble finding it, simply google thatnursecancook green seasoning! 
.
.
.

I feel like the drums or flats argument gets a little irrelevant whenever the wings are hittin’. 🤣I’m partial to flats because flats rule the world but honestly, just pass the wings and give me a ranch dipping sauce! Recipe inside my Dinner in 30 Ebook! Now on SALE‼️Available for immediate download at shopthatnursecancook.com or hit the link in my bio! See previous post for details on how I flipped this recipe. Save it so you can reference it later!

node.text:
Wooyyyy!!! Try nuh hold mi back! Sweet n Sour Chicken wings! That’s how you flip a recipe to meet your needs! I used the recipe for my Sweet n Sour Chicken to make this happen. Instead of diced chicken breasts, I used a bag of party wings. Air fried them to avoid the deep fryer. You can use the recipe or just coat them in cornstarch! I fried about 8 wings at a time on 400 degrees for 30 minutes. 😋 No need to make adjustments to the recipe for the sauce. It’s enough for an entire bag of party wings! Good news!! My ebooks are on SALE this weekend for 25% OFF‼️This recipe is in the Dinner in 30 ebook! Hit the link in my bio to get some good wings started😉
.
.
.
.
.
.
